The group is comprised of professionals who form part of a global Mining Team with staff located in Toronto, Vancouver, London, Sydney, Hong Kong and Tokyo dedicated specifically to advising mining sector clients on mergers, acquisitions, and restructurings, as well as raising equity and debt finance. SPECIFIC ACCOUNTABILITIES OF POSITION: Assist in executing all facets of the group’s mandates. Modelling skills will need to encompass building operating models, merger models and, where relevant, LBO modelling. Must develop an ongoing current awareness of activity, trends and developments in the sector, as well as the corporate and investment banking market. Analysts are responsible for both quantitative and qualitative data analysis and industry research. Maintaining group’s databases on a current basis. It requires dedication, passion for the industry and a very solid work ethic. COMPETENCIES: (Knowledge/Skill Requirements) Undergraduate degree in a (mining) sector related or business-related discipline. Candidate to have experience in creating business development proposals. Client sensitive/service oriented approach. Excellent writing skills, incorporating the ability to explain detailed financial and statistical analyses. The ability to work within a demanding and dynamic team environment. Research Analyst (Economics) APS Level 3 - 12 Months Non-ongoing Full Time $60,601 - $65,349 p.a 15.4% employer superannuation Workplace & Economic Research Section, Tribunal Services Branch Melbourne About the Fair Work Commission The Fair Work Commission (the Commission) is the national workplace relations tribunal. It is an independent body with power to carry out a range of functions relating to: • the safety net of minimum wages and employment conditions • enterprise bargaining • industrial action • dispute resolution • termination of employment • registered organisations. The Commission is a statutory authority with offices in each state and territory. The majority of staff is based in Melbourne, Sydney and Brisbane. The Tribunal Services Branch provides research, project management and administrative support to Commission members. Staff members coordinate the day-to-day support in Members’ Chambers, undertake specialist workplace relations and economic research and assist with managing large statutory reviews, such as of modern awards and the minimum wage. In addition, they perform analysis of draft enterprise agreements, coordinate arbitration hearings for unfair dismissal matters, provide research for individual Members, maintain a workplace relations library and oversee national and international engagement activities. The Workplace and Economic Research Section (the Section) produces externally published and internal research and analysis for the Commission including the President, its Members, the General Manager, the Director of the Tribunal Services Branch and other areas of the Tribunal. The Section, led by the Manager and co-managed by the Manager for Annual Wage Reviews, has a number of specific responsibilities, including supporting: • the Expert Panel for annual wage reviews by undertaking and managing its research program and assisting with the annual wage review process; • providing legal, economic and data analysis and advice to support the President, major cases and Members; and • the General Manager and the Executive to assist the discharge of their statutory functions such as: - services to assist productive and harmonious workplace relations (such as procuring and managing research, undertaking and designing surveys, evaluation of Commission projects and managing other research partnerships); - research to assist budget savings matters (such as workload monitoring and process reviews for teams, public value and benchmarking research, data analysis and reporting to identify cost efficiencies); and - assistance in the preparation of the General Manager’s reporting requirements (s. 653). Employment terms and conditions are derived from the Public Service Act 1999 and the Fair Work Commission Enterprise Agreement 2017-2020. Employees must adhere to the Code of Conduct and behaviour is to be consistent with the Australian Public Service Values. Description of Role As a member of the Section, the Research Analyst undertakes and delivers research and data analysis as well as providing support to the team and the Manager for Annual Wage Reviews. In addition, the Research Analyst may provide support to Members of the Commission and the Executive. As a member of the Section, the Research Analyst contributes to the delivery of services in accordance with statutory requirements and agreed service standards. Duties 1. Drawing on economics expertise, undertake research and analysis on complex, technical issues (including in relation to minimum wages) and, under direction, prepare data analysis, research reports and briefing. 2. Communicate analysis of data on broader economic, social, labour market and other relevant indicators to contribute to briefs, statistical publications, decision drafting and as directed. 3. As a member of the team, actively contribute to team planning and reporting. 4. Provide advice and support to the Manager for Annual Wage Reviews as well as Manager of the Section, Members, the Director, Tribunal Services and the General Manager. 5. Develop and maintain strong working relationships with a range of key internal and external stakeholders. 6. Other duties as directed by the Manager for Annual Wage Reviews, Manager of the Section and/or the Director, Tribunal Services. 11 hours ago - save job - original job View or apply to job Other jobs you may like Research Analyst Fetch Recruitment - Melbourne VIC 1 day ago Research Analyst Swinburne University of Technology - Melbourne VIC 5 hours ago Research Analyst jobs in Melbourne VIC Jobs at Fair Work Commission in Melbourne VIC

Biostatistician (Research Officer) Generation Victoria (GenV) is a new whole-of-state Research initiative led from the Murdoch Children’s Research Institute (MCRI), aiming to transform large-scale Children’s Research in Victoria. We currently require a Full Time Biostatistician (Research Officer) on a 12 month contract to join the GenV Program. This position will be responsible for biostatistical leadership within the Gen V project, as it takes shape over the next few years. The appointee will engage in a broad range of activities related to Gen V, including collaboration with and support for emerging Gen V related research, and to the broader training and translation activities of Clinical Epidemiology & Biostatistics Unit (CEBU). You will also be responsible for: Contributing to the development of the Gen V data repository, by providing expert end-user statistical input. Leading analyses of LifeCourse cohort study data including linked administrative data, to produce research outputs in collaboration with Gen V researchers and to test the data repository structure. Supervision of junior staff performing data cleaning and data preparation, in conjunction with the Gen V IT team. Providing analyst input to discussions and bridging work between Gen V and Royal Children’s Hospital (RCH) data, including potential problems and novel topics arising in modern clinical informatics (e.g. high-density unstructured data and computationally intensive analytics such as machine learning). Liaising constructively between Gen V and the range of analytic and related expertise that already exists within CEBU. Providing advice regarding potential future Gen V initiatives (e.g. grant proposals for pilot studies, early analysis etc.). Contributing to epidemiological research projects as a biostatistical collaborator. Undertaking methodological research that is relevant to primary responsibilities within Gen V and its developing needs. Contributing to the supervision and mentoring of research students. Presenting research seminars at team meetings, workshops and conferences. Contributing to the training and research support activities of CEBU and the GenV team. Key Selection Criteria To be successful in this role you will have: Essential PhD in biostatistics or equivalent research experience with Master of Biostatistics or similar. Experience in applying (and preferably in evaluating or developing) statistical methods for longitudinal epidemiological studies. Excellent statistical computing skills including experience in performing complex data manipulation and statistical analysis using either of the statistical packages R or Stata. Record of postdoctoral research output as evidenced by publication of peer-reviewed scientific articles. Excellent written and verbal communication skills. Demonstrated ability to work independently and collaboratively to achieve project goals and meet agreed deadlines. Familiarity with issues related to health research, principles of confidentiality, privacy, and information handling. Working with Children & National Police Clearance (if appointed) in compliance with the Victorian Governments Child Safety Standards. Only applicants who address the key selection criteria will be considered. Please place your responses to the key selection criteria at the end of your cover letter. For more information on this position please contact: Professor John Carlin: john.carlin@mcri.edu.au Please note, applications will only be considered when submitted via the MCRI website. Contribute to the PM Glynn Institute’s strategic research priorities Undertake research and analysis of quantitative data from a wide range of resources Full time, continuing position based in North Sydney Australian Catholic University (ACU) is an inclusive community which welcomes students and staff of all beliefs. ACU has over 2,500 staff supporting more than 34,000 students across seven campuses – Adelaide, Ballarat, Brisbane, Canberra, Melbourne, North Sydney and Strathfield. As valued members of our community, all staff members are expected to have an understanding of ACU’s mission and values and to demonstrate an active contribution to them. The PM Glynn Institute was established by Australian Catholic University in 2016 to provide the Catholic community with a standing capacity to analyse public policy issues of concern not only to the Catholic Church and its services, but to the wider Australian community as well. The three major focuses for the public policy work of the Institute are the place of religion in secular democratic societies, the future of human rights, and sources of hope in a time of anger and disengagement. The Senior Analyst works closely with Institute staff and project teams to ensure a strong empirical basis for the Institute’s research and policy development in these areas, and for stand-alone projects. As Senior Analyst you will: undertake secondary analysis of quantitative data informed by an understanding of perspectives from the social sciences, such as sociology, economics and demography. initiate and conduct quantitative and qualitative research in support of the Institute’s research priorities lead specific research projects lead or contribute to the writing of research reports, funding applications and collaboration of presentations for project partners and stakeholders. To be successful in the role you will need to demonstrate: post graduate qualifications in an area involving quantitative research such as economics, politics, sociology of religion, demography or statistics excellent quantitative and qualitative research skills extensive experience in public policy work or other relevant areas evidence of ability to show commitment with integrity to the Catholic Identity, Mission and ethos of the University excellent interpersonal and communication skills with an ability to communicate with a range of stakeholders. The University pursues an excellence agenda and offers an environment where staff are welcomed and safe and valued through development, participation and involvement. #Overview The Windows Defender Research team is looking for an experienced Applied ML Data Scientist to join our Melbourne Research Lab. The research team is committed to helping Microsoft customers keep their computers secure against malicious attacks and cybercrime. By continuously gathering and analyzing data, and by working with organizations inside and outside Microsoft, the research team stays agile to combat evolving threats. Our mission is to help protect customers and systems with industry-leading proactive protection, advise customers, and engage in valuable partnerships. More details about team at https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/wdsi As a dedicated Data Scientist on our Research team, you will apply your machine learning expertise to enhance our reputation systems so that we can predict and block cybersecurity threats. You’ll work with the team to identify and build features, create experiments, vet ML models, and ship successful models that provide protection for hundreds of millions of Microsoft customers. At Microsoft, you’ll have access to vast amounts of threat-related data from billions of endpoints and other sources. Our data pipelines are curated and supported by engineering teams (so you won't have to do much data engineering – you get to do the fun stuff.) Microsoft also has many partner teams that have decades of ML expertise and we also offer many company-sponsored classes and conferences that focus on data science and ML. There’s great growth opportunity for data science at Microsoft, and on the research team, you'll be able to apply that expertise to protecting customers, such as consumers like your friends and family to enterprises that have critical assets that need advanced threat protection from targeted attacks. #Responsibilities Develop high-performance machine learning models to predict and classify clean and malicious activity. Identify performant features and models and make them universally accessible to our team and partners across Microsoft. Provide technical leadership to our team by reviewing problem sets, proposing prediction models, and reviewing experiments and models. Act as a resident expert for machine learning, statistics, and experiment design. #Qualifications Basic qualifications: 5+ years of professional experience in experiment design and applied machine learning predicting outcomes in large-scale, complex datasets. Masters or Ph.D degree with coursework in Statistics, Data Science, Experimentation Design, and Machine Learning highly desirable. Preferred qualifications: Proficiency in R, Azure ML, Python, or other statistics/ML tools. Moderate coding skills. SQL or similar required. C# or other languages strongly preferred. Outstanding communication and collaboration skills. Strong drive for results. You have a proven record of shepherding experiments to create successful shipping products/services. Experience with prediction in adversarial (threat) environments highly desirable. Microsoft is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, color, family or medical care leave, gender identity or expression, genetic information, marital status, medical condition, national origin, physical or mental disability, political affiliation, protected veteran status, race, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws, regulations and ordinances. Assisting with maintenance, monitoring and upkeep of adequate laboratory supplies and equipment. Assisting in research and development, including method validation and establishment of new services as directed. Excellent written and verbal communication skills. Ability to work efficiently and professionally both as an individual and as part of a team. Desired: Master of Science or PhD in a relevant discipline. Demonstrable high level of technical competency in molecular and genetic technologies and familiarity with genomic technologies. Demonstrable competency in basic bioinformatics analysis as well as specialised tools that are required for data collection, analysis, and visualisation. Demonstrable experience and competence in the performance and understanding of a wide range of diagnostic tests or procedures. Demonstrable ability in giving professional and appropriate advice on scientific and clinical matters to experts and lay persons. Demonstrated ability to critically assess and evaluate new equipment, instruments or products relevant to diagnostic or research work. The Current Opportunity The Superloop+ Information Security Analyst is part of our Information Security team who assess both ours and our customers environments for compliance against documented industry best practice and standards for architecture, configuration and hardware & software lifecycle management. This is a hands on, technical position however, the Information Security Analyst will be controls focused and responsible for setting and assessing compliance with defined technical standards. As such, the Information Security Analyst is responsible for the quality of data extracted from the technical suite and presented to the customer throughout the security engagements. What we can give you Work here for the same reasons our leaders work here; it’s not just a job for us: Work with and learn from some of the industry’s legends We’re here to buck the status quo Be part of our ongoing success story as our growth only begins to take-off We know when to work-hard but we really know how to play-hard Casual and relaxed environment – ditch the corporate attire Don’t get bogged down with our “Get it done” approach We’re a progressive technology company – flexible working arrangements are assumed Career progression, personal and professional development opportunities as we grow and evolve Opportunity to be part of the innovation and continual improvement of our processes and systems High Performing Traits Passion for cybersecurity Comfortable translating technical terminology into everyday language Naturally empathetic, capable of relating to people from different backgrounds Process-oriented Driven and self-motivated As an IS Analyst (Superloop+), you will Review industry controls based frameworks; Assemble internal customer compliance framework; Perform gap analyses on customer environments against agreed standards; Build and maintain reporting templates based on agreed standards; Develop and implement internal security awareness model, including training and communication strategies; Develop and implement assurance program, to ensure compliance framework meets requirements; Contribute to the creation and and maintenance of security design guidelines for configuration of Superloop+ product suite; Perform technical security tests, including controls audits, gap assessments, security vulnerability testing, behavioural monitoring and anomaly detection; Provide guidance on the implementation of customer security initiatives, assisting where required; Produce technical as-built documentation to detail products and services delivered to customers; and Complete any other duties as directed About you The successful applicant will possess 4+ years with experience in compliance and IT. An in-depth understanding of end-to-end IT systems, including networks, compute, virtualisation and operating systems. Experience working with MSP. Comfortable delivering meaningful presentations to a wide audience Experience writing technical documentation. Excellent research skills. It will also be preferred if you have Industry certification such as ITIL/CREST/OSCP. About Superloop Founded by Bevan Slattery in 2014 and listing on the ASX in 2015, Superloop started out as an infrastructure company designing, constructing and operating carrier-grade dark fibre networks throughout Australia, Singapore and Hong Kong. Superloop has since made a number of strategic acquisitions, including Cinenet, ApexNetworks, BigAir Group, SubPartners, GX2 and NuSkope which expands our competitive capabilities into international submarine connectivity, fixed-wireless, cloud & managed services and cybersecurity. At Superloop the customer is at the centre of everything we do. We strive to always provide an exceptional customer experience from first contact all the way through to contract renewal. We do this through delivering future-focused products, fully supported by our capable and driven teams. We’re a fast-paced and growing company with a start-up feel. We’re led and mentored by industry veterans who love technology and pushing its capabilities to the limits. Each and every one of our valuable team members are dedicated to being at the top of their game and hungry for success. Being part of a team like ours gives you the fantastic opportunity to take ownership of your work and to be truly innovative; in fact, we encourage it! So, what now? If this sounds like a role you’d be perfect for and a team you want to be a part of, apply now! Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted. While we do enjoy working with recruitment agencies, we ask that you do not contact us about this vacancy. One key domain our client focuses on is the Telecom industry. The Telecom industry is going through transformation driven by Network-IT convergence, Virtualisation, Analytics and Machine Learning. As our Client's Client’s businesses scale and accelerates, their challenges become increasingly complex whilst requiring responsive and informed decision-making. The Data Scientist is a key contributor in unravelling the most complex problems that are inevitably multi-variant and ecosystem-wide. As part of the analytics lab, you are responsible for driving the thinking and communication of how our client uses advanced analytics techniques to solve problems in innovative ways. You will be working closely with business data analysts, subject matter experts and the data engineering team to deliver sometimes profound analytical insights in short timeframes. You are a fast learner and a confident self-starter; naturally curious and passionate about technology, but with varied interests; and an excellent communicator who yearns to work with a small group of skilled practitioners. Summaries: About us Orygen, The National Centre of Excellence in Youth Mental Health is the world’s leading research and knowledge translation organisation focusing on mental ill-health in young people. About the role The Biostatistician/Statistician/Applied Data Analyst will be responsible for the extraction, cleaning, analysis, and interpretation of psychometric data obtained through the research activities of a major NHMRC funded Partnership Grant. This grant focuses on developing youth-specific change and outcome measures for effective youth mental health service delivery. The Biostatistician/Statistician/Applied Data Analyst, under the supervision of the Chief Investigator, will manage the data from each of the four projects under this grant, which collectively aim to develop new measures of change and outcome and implement these in a range of mental health service settings and to evaluate the effectiveness of treatment in these services. The Biostatistician/Statistician/Applied Data Analyst will work in close collaboration with the Chief and Associate Investigators in addition to research, evaluation and key mental health service staff as required. The Biostatistician/Statistician/Applied Data Analyst will manage datasets pertaining to service use, outcome measure validation, and fidelity, gathered from multiple sites across Australia. Additionally, the Biostatistician/Statistician/Applied Data Analyst will be required to contribute towards academic publications of project data and related research, as well as attend regular research and supervision meetings to monitor progress and development of the study outcomes. The Biostatistician/Statistician/Applied Data Analyst will report to, and work under the direction of Chief Investigator Professor Sue Cotton, who in turn reports to the Chair of Youth Mental Health. About you To be considered for this role you will need: Postgraduate (honours level) qualification in either the behavioural, social sciences, statistics and/or other related discipline. Demonstrated experience working with, and conducting analyses of large psychometric datasets. Demonstrated proficiency in data entry, data management, and data analysis. Intermediate to advanced knowledge and experience in the use of statistical analyses software, particularly IBM® SPSS® Statistics or Stata. Demonstrated ability in contributing towards research publications, particularly in the field of health/mental health. Demonstrated administrative and organisational skills including the ability to set priorities and meet deadlines. Demonstrated ability to work both independently and collaboratively. Excellent oral and written communication skills and interpersonal skills. Competence in the use of Excel, Word, and other Microsoft Office Suite programs. Company Description Headquartered in the UK and Australia, ThinkMarkets is an industry leading brokerage with a global presence, with headquarters in London and Melbourne, as well as hubs in the Asia-Pacific, the Middle East and North Africa, Europe, and the Americas. The firm is authorized and regulated by the FCA, and fully registered with ASIC. ThinkMarkets specializes in foreign exchange (FX), metals and global CFD trading, as well as spread betting. Dedicated to delivering high-quality execution and service to an ever growing range of traders, ThinkMarkets has been named “Best Broker Australia” by the World Finance Awards, “Best New Contributor” by FXStreet and “Best Forex Broker in Asia” at the China Forex Expo. The firm recently acquired Trade Interceptor, the world’s most searched-for trading analysis app. The deal marks a major step forward in ThinkMarkets’ mission to be the only truly mobile retail broker – a crucial commitment given the rapid growth of the mobile trading market. As well as providing 24/5 customer support, ThinkMarkets also provide a full suite of tutorial seminars, webinars, and videos as part of their cornerstone ThinkMarkets University. As the Quantitative Analyst you will be working closely with the trading and risk management teams with a core focus on pricing models. You will be working on the development of execution algorithms, product pricing, and analysis of large tick datasets. Ideally, you will have worked with derivatives in the past and will have a strong quantitative background, including work with time-series analysis, Statistics , MiniTab , Tableau and Excel. You will be responsible for critical pricing decisions across the entire order book from FX , Indices, Equities , Commodities , Futures and Other Assets. In addition, the candidate will have experience in all aspects of the Financial Services industry such as analysis of order books, trade processing, and/or market data. The candidate will have some programming skills in C#, C++ or Java, but not necessarily to full 'developer' level. Candidate must have strong experience in Tableau , Qlik , Minitab , MatLab and Advanced Statistics. Responsibilities Develop short-term trading strategies based on trading patterns of accounts, pricing, and other market data. Systematically analyze market tick data to create intraday and short-term pricing models Contribute to ThinkMarkets’ overall research efforts in pricing by interacting with and collaborating trading and risk management teams. Requirements 2-5 years' work experience in researching and trading short-term trading strategies in FX and Futures space. High Frequency / Market making experience are also welcomed. A bachelor’s, master’s, or PhD degree in computer science, mathematics, or a hard-science from a top university. An advanced degree in computer science is a plus. Experience with scientific computing, algorithm development, or pattern recognition. A background in developing high-performance, multi-threaded applications. Strong programming skills (Java, C, or C++) & scripting languages (Perl, Python, UNIX shell). We recognise the importance of balance and embrace agility, understanding that this means different things to each and every one of our employees. We will not be reviewing any applications during this time, however we will do our best to give you an update as we return to the office. If you have any questions regarding this role you can contact Juliette Jamoneau in the Talent Acquisition Team on 02 8260 4149 after the 15th January . We look forward to hearing from you and wish you a wonderful festive season! Chatham Financial is a global financial risk management advisory services and technology solutions firm serving clients in many areas, including: Interest rate, foreign currency, and commodity risk management and hedging, Derivative and Hedge accounting and financial reporting/disclosure, Regulatory compliance, and Debt and derivatives valuations. As a purpose-driven organization, we are committed to making a positive impact for our clients, our colleagues, our communities and the capital markets at large. We are an employee-owned, view-neutral services firm, with no affiliation to any financial institution allowing us to serve as independent advisors. Chatham has worked hard to create a distinct work environment that values people, teamwork, integrity and client service. We always strive to do what is right, just and fair, even when no one is looking. We would rather be governed by principles than rules. We believe leadership should be gained through influence and personal character, not by title or tenure. As a result, we have a non-hierarchical, team-oriented organization that is highly collaborative. Overview For graduating or recent college graduates looking to be challenged in a purpose-driven company that strives to cultivate trust and transparency with clients and among colleagues, Chatham Financial is a full-service financial advisory & technology solutions provider that takes an unexpected approach to developing individuals into successful and impactful financial professionals. We provide individuals intellectually challenging, thought-provoking work in finance that stretches and develops them. Because we have built a successful global financial services business that works with world-class companies in solving complex problems, Chathamites at the start of their careers take on meaningful work as they progress through a steep learning curve supported by a strong team network. This approach gives motivated, self-starters the opportunities to interact regularly with high-level leaders during client engagements, as well as learn from and collaborate with colleagues who are expert practitioners. The Chatham environment encourages fast personal growth and the development of solid financial acumen in debt, derivatives and risk management. Chatham focuses on making impact beyond the financial bottom line by creating positive impact in our markets, with our clients, our fellow employees, and our communities, while fostering a unique culture with strong camaraderie. This camaraderie encourages on-the-job teamwork and engagement beyond the day-to-day through opportunities for community service, regular social interaction and team-oriented company events and activities. Chatham values the whole employee, including life outside of work and personal interests, and this caring and support results in an upbeat and relationally-oriented environment. As a result, people feel empowered and supported, knowing that Chatham values each person as an individual, not just for the work they do, but for the contributions they make toward fulfilling our purposes. Role Within our Advisory Services practice, we offer analysts a multitude of opportunities to start their career path in becoming a subject matter expert. Both the learning experience and business environment are highly dynamic, therefore the analyst role and career path are dynamic and evolving. The career stories of our most experienced consultants are diverse, reflecting success at Chatham does not follow a single thread. Among leaders, we have individuals that have worked in the same practice area and with the same client base their entire career, as well as individuals that have rotated through several of the advisory practices. The consistent theme in success stories at Chatham is passion and commitment to learning, delivering, and serving. Our Australian team is currently in search of an analyst to function in a multi-faceted role. The team is small, fostering a pragmatic, hands-on approach to client deliverables. Some of the service areas this will touch include: Chatham’s Hedging practice advises clients on interest rate, foreign currency, and commodity hedging across industries and sectors spanning: real estate, private equity, ASX 100, and Fortune 1000 corporations, and financial institutions. Hedging teams across these sectors execute more than $450 billion in hedging transactions annually. Analysts will gain a thorough understanding of derivative products and markets by focusing on pre and post-trade activities as they move towards client advisory and direct client interface. Learning takes place alongside experienced team members in an apprenticeship-style format to: Structure and model derivative transactions. Prepare and review transaction documents to assist with transaction execution, legal and regulatory compliance. Assist with client and market research, as well as preparation of client deliverables. The Complex Advisory team serves primarily corporate clients, outside of our Real Estate and Financial Institutions sectors. Most of our work is project based, and is designed to provide clients with deliverables that quantify financial risk, assess current risk management programs, and/or develop appropriate hedge strategies and policies. Project scope ranges from several days to several months, with project needs varying accordingly. The complex advisory team is often required to navigate extensive amounts of data, understand the application of complex economic and accounting constraints, apply real-world best practices around hedging strategy, and deliver actionable recommendations and findings to our clients. ChathamDirect team members work with new clients to onboard them to the powerful ChathamDirect platform. Tasks will include: Project Management – Learn and apply the ChathamDirect Project Management framework and all of its components. This includes effectively communicating individual task status to clients. System Configuration – Performing general and client specific setup tasks in ChathamDirect. Data Migration & Reconciliation – Input Data, and analyze and present to client any differences in output between client and Chatham systems. Integration with External Systems – Ensuring that connectivity is tested and error free. Setting Up Reports – Working with clients to ensure that report output meets their expectations. Training clients on using the system – This would take place either onsite or via web meeting. Qualifications Due to the variety of projects the team encounters, it’s important that the composition of the team includes a variety of skill sets and experience levels, with some of the key skills noted below: Quantitative skills: the ability to work with large amounts of data and understand causal relationships, attention to detail in both inputs and outputs, experience with statistical analysis and financial modeling Communication skills: the ability to communicate complex subject matter in a way that educates and prioritizes findings, flexing delivery style to accommodate different audiences, engaging with clients on new project proposals and ongoing delivery, effective communication through various formats (PowerPoint slides, email, verbal, spreadsheets, etc.) Collaboration skills: the ability to share information internally to grow the capabilities of the team and to seek out knowledge from others when needed, partnering with external clients throughout a project, delivering on internal requirements to support other teams as needed Project management skills: the ability to prioritize competing demands and align resources with project deliverables, communicating internal and external expectations throughout a project A combination of these skills will be utilized by every team member, but we expect individual roles to draw out individual strengths that complement the team. Our goal is to develop people so that they can achieve greater responsibilities, and have impact on those around them, clients and teammates alike. 25 days ago - save job - original job View or apply to job Other jobs you may like IT Risk Analyst NavigosSearch - Melbourne VIC 30+ days ago IT Risk Analyst en world - Melbourne VIC 30+ days ago Credit Risk Analyst Aston Carter - Melbourne City Centre VIC 19 days ago Performance Analyst Michael Page - Melbourne Eastern Suburbs VIC Michael Page AU - 13 days ago Risk Analytics Analyst/Senior Analyst Deloitte - Melbourne VIC 18 days ago Financial Risk Analyst jobs in Melbourne VIC Jobs at Chatham Financial in Melbourne VIC

OVERVIEW OF JOB Wavemaker (formerly MEC) is looking for a strong Digital Manager to join our largest brand team in Australia . The successful candidate will work on a wide range of market leading and dynamic campaigns with a focus on brand performance and results driven work. As a team they are used to a fast paced working style, while being hugely exciting, you will need to think smart and act fast. REPORTING OF THE ROLE This role reports in to the Digital Director. 3 BEST THINGS ABOUT THE ROLE: Influence the development of digital media strategies for globally recognized brands serving as the key client contact for brand managers Develop the skills essential for a digital marketer including exposure to programmatic, social, search and emerging platforms Grow and nourish your career by supporting the role out of an industry leading DMP solution MEASURES OF SUCCESS – In three months: Nailed the client structure & started to immerse yourself in the category Started to build relationships with our key client contacts Have established a great way of working with the legends in the team at Wavemaker Understand the 2018 strategy, strategic pillars and segment across your brands In six months: Established strong and trust based relationship with your clients as a digital expert Solid relationship with all the internal teams at Wavemaker and understand who to engage and how to get the best from them to help with a response Be able to persuade with influence and story tell to sell through ideas Have a number of presentations to your key clients under your belt, leveraging the world class Wavemaker planning process In 12 months: Sold in a growth opportunity (diversified s ervice, innovation, media first ) Mentor ed and develop ed the digital skills and knowledge of junior team members RESPONSIBILITIES OF THE ROLE: As a Digital Manager you will be a key contact for our clients and will be responsible for developing media recommendations and managing the delivery of all digital campaign s with the support of an Executive and Analyst. This includes the planning, implementation, optimisations and reporting of campaigns across your client portfolio. You will be responsible for building strong client relationships, taking client briefs and producing high standard, effective/efficient and profitable digital campaigns across our client portfolio. Each and every campaign from your team should follow industry best practice, challenge client thinking and incorporate the latest innovations and opportunities across digital. As a manager, you will be responsible for managing the development of the digital team to reach the same level of expertise through the campaign experience. WHAT YOU WILL NEED: We are looking for someone who is a passionate self-starter who is not afraid to roll up their sleeves and get their hands dirty. You will need to be resourceful, agile and enjoy working in a fast-paced environment. Strong work ethic and proficient time management skills are essential. You will have the ability to turn data and campaign analysis into compelling stories. Previous social, programmatic and search exp osure also preferred to weave the digital landscape into each response. As strong communicator with a professional approach to all people you come in contact with both internally and externally. Digital is a part of your DNA and you will have an informed point of view on developments and opportunities within the advertising industry. Keeping up to date with industry trends and innovation is a keen interest to you. You will have strong attention to detail, financial and numerical astuteness as a key part of the job will be working in in data heavy platforms. ABOUT WAVEMAKER Wavemaker is a billion-dollar revenue agency that sits at the heart of GroupM and WPP. Our ambition is to be the most distinctive and admired media, content, and technology agency in the world. Wavemaker is a global network that operates locally in over 90 countries and 139 offices.
